@startuml
title Seller Quality Analysis Using Watson NLU - Control Flow

actor User
participant "Jupyter Notebook" as Notebook
database "Db2 Database" as Db2
participant "Watson NLU" as NLU
participant "Data Processing Pipeline" as Pipeline
participant "Embedded Dashboard" as Dashboard

User -> Notebook: Execute notebook
activate Notebook

Notebook -> Db2: Connect to database
activate Db2
Db2 --> Notebook: Connection established
deactivate Db2

Notebook -> Pipeline: Initialize data processing pipeline
activate Pipeline

Pipeline -> Db2: Load customer review data
activate Db2
Db2 --> Pipeline: Return raw review data
deactivate Db2

Pipeline -> Pipeline: Extract and clean data
Pipeline -> Pipeline: Preprocess reviews

loop For each customer review
    Pipeline -> NLU: Send review text for analysis
    activate NLU
    NLU -> NLU: Perform sentiment analysis
    NLU -> NLU: Perform emotion analysis (joy, sadness, anger)
    NLU --> Pipeline: Return sentiment and emotion scores
    deactivate NLU
end

Pipeline -> Pipeline: Analyze delivery performance
Pipeline -> Pipeline: Compare estimated vs actual delivery dates
Pipeline -> Pipeline: Calculate delivery timeliness score

Pipeline -> Pipeline: Calculate overall seller quality rating (0-5 stars)
Pipeline -> Pipeline: Generate optimized dataset for visualization

Pipeline --> Notebook: Return processed data with seller ratings
deactivate Pipeline

Notebook -> Dashboard: Load dashboard configuration
activate Dashboard
Dashboard -> Dashboard: Read dashboard.json

Notebook -> Dashboard: Send processed data for visualization
Dashboard -> Dashboard: Generate interactive visualizations
Dashboard -> Dashboard: Display seller and product performance

Dashboard --> User: Present insights and analytics
deactivate Dashboard

deactivate Notebook

@enduml
